509
00:19:18,658 --> 00:19:20,988
Now I'm never gonna
make it to Nantucket.

510
00:19:21,027 --> 00:19:23,097
(Marvin continues wailing)

511
00:19:25,031 --> 00:19:29,071
(explosions)

512
00:19:29,101 --> 00:19:30,901
Oh, look a
fireworks display.

513
00:19:30,937 --> 00:19:32,337
Some rockets
red glare action.

514
00:19:32,372 --> 00:19:33,712
Thank God.

515
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:37,210
Thought my glaucoma drops
were causing a reaction.

516
00:19:37,244 --> 00:19:41,314
Marvin, I'm so sorry this
whole journey's been a bummer.

517
00:19:41,348 --> 00:19:46,548
Soon you'll be right back in
Mommy's arms, as warm as summer.

518
00:19:46,586 --> 00:19:50,016
But sadly while your troubles
stop once we get to the inn

519
00:19:50,056 --> 00:19:53,386
the moment we arrive
is when my troubles will begin.

520
00:19:53,426 --> 00:19:55,926
Sometimes daddies screw up,

521
00:19:55,962 --> 00:19:58,772
sometimes mommies get upset.

522
00:19:58,798 --> 00:20:02,198
I really hope this weekend
is a memory you'll forget.

523
00:20:02,235 --> 00:20:05,905
So look up at those fireworks,
enjoy the falling embers...

524
00:20:05,938 --> 00:20:09,408
NARRATOR:
And that, kids,
is the very first thing

525
00:20:09,442 --> 00:20:12,612
your cousin
Marvin remembers.

526
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:18,919
Gentlemen and ladies,
it'll be an hour or so...

527
00:20:18,951 --> 00:20:20,891
(groans)
before the truck
gets here to give our

528
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,560
broken bus a tow.

529
00:20:22,589 --> 00:20:26,129
So in the meantime I suggest
we all get nice and cozy.

530
00:20:26,158 --> 00:20:28,658
We're gonna be here
for a while.

531
00:20:30,297 --> 00:20:32,867
Uh, ring-around-the-rosy?

532
00:20:32,899 --> 00:20:34,899
Yeah!

533
00:20:34,934 --> 00:20:38,044
How far do you suppose it is
to the Farhampton Inn?

534
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:40,040
I'd say about five miles away.

535
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:41,912
Oh, no.

536
00:20:41,941 --> 00:20:43,481
What's with the grin?

537
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:45,450
NARRATOR:
Then Marshall
looked up heavenward,

538
00:20:45,478 --> 00:20:47,478
and swore by night's first star

539
00:20:47,514 --> 00:20:49,884
five simple words
he'd soon regret:

540
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,446
I can walk that far.

